# Project Workflow

This project uses the following workflow:

Local Files
→ Git Commit (save milestone)
→ Git Push to GitHub
→ Automatic deployment by Vercel
→ Public URL updated

Never create GitHub Releases.

Never publish packages.

Never use GitHub Pages.

The only deployment target for this project is Vercel.

When the user asks to publish, launch, deploy, release or put the application online:

1. Save pending work with a git commit if necessary.
2. Push the latest commit to GitHub.
3. Wait for Vercel to deploy automatically.
4. Verify deployment if possible.
5. Present the Vercel URL.

Assume that pushing to GitHub is the deployment trigger.
